BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 21 (XINHUA) -- U.S. Defense Secretary 
William Perry arrived in Tokyo today from Seoul for a two-day 
visit to Japan for talks with Japanese Government leaders. 
  Perry will meet with Japanese Defense Agency Director 
General 
Kazuo Aichi this evening and Foreign Minister Tsutomu Hata 
tomorrow, Japanese officials said. 
  He is expected to discuss with the Japanese leaders policy 
coordination to deal with possible hostilities as concern 
deepens over Pyongyang's refusal to allow full international 
inspections of it nuclear facilities. 

